
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Questions";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_UserHelp.cshtml";
    ViewBag._NavFAQ = "active";
}

<div class="faq-wrap" id="accordion-col-1">
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <h2 class="pageTitle">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="panel-group">
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseOne" class="collapsed" aria-expanded="false"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 1. What marketplaces are supported by My PPC Pal?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse" aria-expanded="false" style="height: 0px;">
                            <div class="panel-body">Currently we are only working on the Amazon.com Marketplace (US).</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseTwo" class="collapsed" aria-expanded="false"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 2. Will My PPC Pal lower my ACoS?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse" aria-expanded="false" style="height: 0px;">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                My PPC Pal was made to help automate the task of optimizing your PPC spend on Amazon.com. If you do not currently stay on top of your advertising campaigns MPP will likely yield favorable results. However, due to so many outside factors (product niche, listing quality, competition, pricing, etc.), no results can be guaranteed
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseThree" class="collapsed" aria-expanded="false"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 3. How does My PPC Pal make optimization decisions?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse" aria-expanded="false" style="height: 0px;">
                            <div class="panel-body">You can select one of our preset optimization formulas or create your own fully customized formulas for optimization. Once your rules are set up per campaign, MPP will use these filters to make optimizations.</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseFour"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 4. I only want to lower my ACoS, which formula should I use?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                If your only goal for advertising is to have a very low ACoS, we suggest creating a custom formula rather than using one of our preset formulas. Our preset formulas were created to maximize advertising sales, to increase organic rank and customer reach.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseFive"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 5. What are the numbers for the preset formulas?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseFive" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                The numbers behind our preset formulas are proprietary and we cannot tell you exactly what they are. These formulas are based on what has worked best for our own campaigns and clients’ campaigns in the past. Our approach on advertising on Amazon is to get as much exposure as possible, increase sales to rank higher organically.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseSix"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 6. I am brand new to Amazon PPC, which formula should I use?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseSix" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                We suggest using the “Recommended” formula to anyone who is brand new to Amazon PPC. If your product is also brand new and you want to give it an extra push in the beginning to help it rank better organically and gain some initial reviews, we recommend the “Aggressive” formula. If you have a more limited budget and just want to test the waters of PPC try the “Conservative” formula first.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseSeven"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 7. Is My PPC Pal a robot?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseSeven" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                My PPC Pal is part robot, and part human. It was created by an Amazon PPC Consultant and 7-Figure Amazon seller to help him to further grow his business and automate the repetitive tasks involved with optimizing Sponsored Product Campaigns.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="panel-group">
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseEight" class="collapsed" aria-expanded="false"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 8. Does My PPC Pal work with AMS?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseEight" class="panel-collapse collapse" aria-expanded="false">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                No, currently My PPC Pal only works with Amazon Sponsored Products. This is the main ad platform for Amazon Sellers accessible through the “Campaign Manager” section under your seller central account.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseNine" class="collapsed" aria-expanded="false"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 9. How should I set up my campaigns?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseNine" class="panel-collapse collapse" aria-expanded="false" style="height: 0px;">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                Yes, My PPC Pal will start to make changes on your behalf to any campaign new or existing, once you have created the rules for optimization in MPP.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseTen" class="collapsed" aria-expanded="false"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 10. Will My PPC Pal work with existing campaigns?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseTen" class="panel-collapse collapse" aria-expanded="false" style="height: 0px;">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                Yes, My PPC Pal will start to make changes on your behalf to any campaign new or existing, once you have created the rules for optimization in MPP.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseEleven" class="collapsed" aria-expanded="false"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 11. How often will may campaigns be optimized?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseEleven" class="panel-collapse collapse" aria-expanded="false">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                My PPC Pal will make most optimizations daily, and will make bid amount adjustments and add negative exact keywords based on poorly performing customer search terms weekly.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseTwelve" class="collapsed" aria-expanded="false"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 12. Do I have to approve all changes which are made to my campaigns?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseTwelve" class="panel-collapse collapse" aria-expanded="false">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                No, My PPC Pal is an automation tool. You set up rules for each campaign, then you get to go back to business while we make the optimizations for you on your behalf.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseThirteen" class="collapsed" aria-expanded="false"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 13. There are words I want to bid on regardless of the cost of bids, how should I set these up?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseThirteen" class="panel-collapse collapse" aria-expanded="false">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                We recommend setting up a separate campaign for your highly competitive keywords which you want to bid on regardless of how high the ACoS/Ad Spend is and either turn this campaign off for all optimizations, or set up extremely high formulas for cut off points on this campaign to protect your wallet from this campaign going completely rouge.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title"><a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion-col-1" href="#collapseFourteen" class="collapsed" aria-expanded="false"><i class="fa fa-comments-o"></i> 14. How long does it take My PPC Pal to import new campaigns from Amazon?</a></h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseFourteen" class="panel-collapse collapse" aria-expanded="false">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                Brand new campaigns will usually show up in My PPC Pal after two days have passed since it was created in Seller Central. Amazon has to provide reporting on the new campaign in the bulk operations before My PPC Pal recognizes them. Note: For Amazon to provide reporting, campaigns must have activity. (clicks, impressions).
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clear"></div>
</div>
